> I am under the impression that it's a docker bug? docker pull works just fine but manifest inspect does errors out.

Thanks for checking, guys! I see. But when creating an image by Docker, the `docker manifest inspect` works for the image. The reproducer is below.

```
$ docker --version
Docker version 20.10.17, build aa7e414

$ docker build --rm -t quay.io/junaruga/report-docker-20.10.17-image-compatibility-busybox:latest .

$ docker push quay.io/junaruga/report-docker-20.10.17-image-compatibility-busybox:latest
```

Here is the registry page.
https://quay.io/repository/junaruga/report-docker-20.10.17-image-compatibility-busybox?tab=info

Then the `docker manifest inspect` works.

```
$ docker manifest inspect quay.io/junaruga/report-docker-20.10.17-image-compatibility-busybox:latest
{
  "schemaVersion": 2,
  "mediaType": "application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.v2+json",
